# 1) Copy this file to github-mcp.env (gitignored):
#    cp .cursor/github-mcp.env.example .cursor/github-mcp.env
#
# 2) Create a PAT (classic or fine-grained) with repo read + read:org as needed:
#    https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
#
# 3) Paste the token after the = sign on the line below (no quotes).
#
# 4) Restart Cursor after saving.
#
# This file is loaded by Cursor only for STDIO MCP servers that set envFile
# (see .cursor/mcp.json → github → Docker). Remote GitHub MCP cannot use
# envFile; use Bearer ${env:GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN} and set the var
# in an environment Cursor inherits (e.g. launch Cursor from a shell where
# you exported it), or install Docker Desktop and keep the Docker-based config.
GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=
